reviews.review_text:
complete for completists, this is tops.  we have all the joan baez "scare" (dolgushkin), kesey's complete "gong bong" and the chinese joke plus bobo's invite to breakfast.

not only that, there is solid sound unlike the muffled board that i've had for years.  this is still one of my top 20.  that playin-> terrapin-> playin' is outta sight!
Best Show of '81 No fucking doubt. Phil's a little low in all the source tapes. I'll try the 24 bit and see how that sounds, but this Miller is a work of art.

Hell of a 2nd Set Can't say I'm a huge fan of Joan Baez, but I've got respect for her. That said, I don't think her singing meshes very well w/ the Dead's playing or Garcia's voice.

GDTR>Dew into Darkstar? Friggin' amazing!

a very good year Jerry is in peak form. Cold Rain, Terrapin, Going Down, Dew (was Jaw dropping) and Bertha are  excellent versions..1981 Greek and Oakland shows were the best from those venues, an excellent scene
